        "FIGREF0": {
            "text": "1.A blanket ban on IBR, and all forms of contralateral balancing/risk-reducing and revisional/tertiary procedures.2. Where delay is neither feasible nor desirable, opting for simple and expedient surgery should be considered e.g.: a) Expanded use of therapeutic mammaplasty: as a unilateral procedure in selected cases instead of mastectomy and IBR. b) Exploring less technically demanding (albeit \"controversial\") implant-based forms of IBR: i. Epipectoral breast reconstruction (fixed volume implants): this adds about 30 minutes to the ablative surgery as the pre-prepared implant-ADM complex is easily secured with minimal sutures.",
